briefdescription.para: Returns the type used by a quantity to store its values.

simplesect.para: The element type. Possible values are kOCNumberFloatType, kOCNumberDoubleType, kOCNumberFloatComplexType, and kOCNumberDoubleComplexType.

briefdescription.para: Tests if quantity has a specific element type.
Tests if quantity has a complex element type.
Returns size (in bytes) of a quantity element.
Tests if quantity has a specific dimensionality.
Determines if two quantities have the same reduced dimensionality exponents.
Determines if two quantities have the same dimensionality exponents.
Returns the best element type for the two input quantities.

detaileddescription.para:
input1
The first numberType.
input2
The second numberType.
The best numberType from the two quantities.
Returns the best element type for the two input quantities which loses no precision when the quantities are combined in any way: add, subtract, multiply, divide. Input element types and outputs are:
(float complex and float complex) => float complex
(float complex and double complex) => double complex
(double complex and double complex) => double complex

briefdescription.para: Returns larger element type for the two input quantities.

simplesect.para: The larger numberType of the two quantities.

briefdescription.para: Returns smaller element type for the two input quantities.

simplesect.para: The smaller numberType of the two quantities.
